  "id": "019d286a-f2d8-78b2-92cd-6ba005d40597",
  "content": "### AstChunker (corvia-adapter-git)\n### MarkdownChunker (corvia-kernel)\n\n### ConfigChunker (corvia-kernel)\n\n**Formats:** .toml, .yaml, .yml, .json\n\n- `chunk()`: Top-level key/section chunking. Each `[section]` in TOML, each top-level key in JSON/YAML.\n- `split_oversized()`: Recurse into nested keys.\n- `merge_small()`: Returns None — kernel default.\n- `overlap_context()`: Prepend parent key path.\n\n\n### PdfChunker (corvia-kernel)\n\n**Formats:** .pdf\n\n- `chunk()`: Page-based extraction → paragraph splitting. Adjacent paragraphs on same page merge up to budget.\n- `split_oversized()`: Sentence-level splitting within paragraph.\n- `merge_small()`: Returns None — kernel default.\n- `overlap_context()`: Returns None (domain adapters can override via FormatRegistry).\n\nPDF dependency: pure Rust crate (`pdf-extract` or `lopdf`). Feature-gated if heavy.\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-02-m3.3-embedding-chunking-design.md",
